🌺 Iris Flower Classification – Naïve Bayes Model



A Machine Learning project using Naïve Bayes Classifier to classify Iris flower species based on their sepal and petal dimensions.

📌 Project Overview
🌱 Dataset: Iris Dataset (from Scikit-Learn)
🧠 Algorithm: Naïve Bayes (GaussianNB)
🌼 Target Classes:

Iris Setosa 🌿
Iris Versicolor 🌺
Iris Virginica 🌾
🎯 Goal: Predict the species of an Iris flower based on sepal/petal length & width.
📊 Dataset Details
The Iris dataset contains 150 samples with four features and one target variable:

Sepal Length (cm)	Sepal Width (cm)	Petal Length (cm)	Petal Width (cm)	Species
5.1	3.5	1.4	0.2	Setosa
4.9	3.0	1.4	0.2	Setosa
4.7	3.2	1.3	0.2	Setosa

Total Samples: 150
Classes: 3 (Setosa, Versicolor, Virginica)
🚀 Technologies Used
✅ Python 🐍
✅ Pandas, NumPy – Data Processing
✅ Scikit-Learn – Naïve Bayes Classifier
✅ Matplotlib, Seaborn – Data Visualization

📈 Model Performance
Metric	Value
Accuracy	~95%
Precision	High
Recall	High
F1-Score	High
🔹 Gaussian Naïve Bayes (GNB) is used since the features are continuous.
